title: The true mayde of the south: or, A rare example of a maide dvvelling at Rie in Sussex, who for the loue of a young man of Lester-shire, went beyond sea in the habit of a page, and after, to their hearts content, were both marryed at Magrum in Germany, and now dwelling at Rye aforesaid. To the tune of, Come, come my sweet and bonny one.
